WEBVTT

00:01.167 --> 00:03.667
[ WAVES CRASHING ]

00:05.000 --> 00:11.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:12.700 --> 00:15.033
Johnathan:
I'VE DONE THIS FOR SO LONG, MAN.

00:16.900 --> 00:18.967
37 YEARS.

00:20.767 --> 00:24.167
HANG ON, HANG ON!
GET DOWN!

00:24.967 --> 00:28.100
YOU WANT TO BE
A CRAB FISHERMAN, DO YOU?

00:28.100 --> 00:30.233
WELL, THIS IS IT.

00:31.967 --> 00:33.200
[ ALARM BLARING ]

00:33.200 --> 00:35.167
HERE WE GO!
WE GOTTA BE SOMEWHERE ELSE.

00:35.167 --> 00:36.567
IT AIN'T BEEN EASY.

00:36.567 --> 00:38.133
YOU SAVED MY [BLEEP]

00:43.100 --> 00:45.667
YOU WANT TO BATTLE
TILL THE VERY END.

00:47.267 --> 00:48.433
HANG ON, GUYS.

00:48.433 --> 00:50.700
WHOO! JACKPOT!

00:50.700 --> 00:54.833
OUR LAST SEASON, WE WANT TO
GO OUT WITH PRIDE, DIGNITY...

00:55.700 --> 00:58.567
YEAH, BABY! [ LAUGHS ]

00:58.567 --> 01:01.433
WE LOVE YOU,
CAPTAIN JOHNATHAN!

01:01.433 --> 01:04.533
Man: YEAH, JOHNATHAN!

01:04.533 --> 01:07.567
WE WANT TO PARK THE BOAT
AND WALK AWAY LIKE CHAMPIONS.

01:20.433 --> 01:23.433
-- Captions by VITAC --
www.vitac.com

01:23.433 --> 01:26.467
CAPTIONS PAID FOR BY
DISCOVERY COMMUNICATIONS

01:29.633 --> 01:33.067
[ WIND HOWLING ]

01:33.067 --> 01:37.633
[ PHONE RINGING ]

01:37.633 --> 01:39.667
TIME BANDIT.

01:39.667 --> 01:42.267
Keith: TIME BANDIT?
WIZARD.

01:42.267 --> 01:44.200
HEY, KEITH.
WHAT DO YOU GOT GOING ON?

01:44.200 --> 01:46.367
DO YOU THINK YOU'LL HAVE
ENOUGH CRAB

01:46.367 --> 01:48.133
TO FINISH
YOUR SEASON THERE?

01:48.133 --> 01:50.467
Narrator: FIVE WEEKS INTO
THE WINTER SEASON...

01:50.467 --> 01:52.933
I'M GONNA TRY TO GET IT DONE
RIGHT HERE, YOU KNOW.

01:52.933 --> 01:55.500
SO, I'M GONNA FINISH
MY SURVEY UP HERE.

01:55.500 --> 01:57.633
BUT HOPEFULLY, IT DOESN'T
JUST DRY UP ON ME.

01:57.633 --> 01:59.267
SO I'LL LET YOU KNOW.

01:59.267 --> 02:01.767
TWO VETERAN CAPTAINS
ARE IN THE FINAL STRETCH

02:01.767 --> 02:04.267
OF THEIR OPILIO MARATHON.

02:04.267 --> 02:05.833
Johnathan:
HOW YOU DOING?

02:05.833 --> 02:08.199
HOPEFULLY WE'RE GONNA HAVE
A GOOD PICK THROUGH THE GEAR,

02:08.199 --> 02:11.133
AND WITH ANY LUCK, WE'LL HAVE
THIS SEASON WRAPPED UP HERE.

02:11.133 --> 02:14.433
ONE CAPTAIN IS GETTING READY
TO CALL IT A YEAR.

02:15.933 --> 02:17.267
AND THE OTHER?

02:17.267 --> 02:18.767
MY LAST SEASON.

02:18.767 --> 02:20.200
A CAREER.

02:20.200 --> 02:22.400
I CAN'T WAIT
TO GET HOME, MAN.

02:22.400 --> 02:24.867
YEAH, HEY, LOOK. I'M GONNA
BUY YOU A ROCKING CHAIR.

02:24.867 --> 02:26.567
I'M GETTING YOU
A ROCKING CHAIR, OKAY?

02:26.567 --> 02:28.533
[ LAUGHS ]

02:28.533 --> 02:30.867
[ LAUGHS ]
THAT'S ALL I'M DOING, BUDDY.

02:30.867 --> 02:32.467
-OKAY.
-I'M SO FAR GONE.

02:32.467 --> 02:33.767
[ LAUGHS ]

02:35.500 --> 02:39.667
SO, ANYWAY, SOUNDS LIKE IT'S
GONNA BLOW LIKE HELL OUT HERE.

02:39.667 --> 02:43.267
GONNA BE 31-FOOT SEAS
AND BLOW EAST-NORTHEAST 55.

02:43.267 --> 02:46.333
BUT THEY STILL HAVE
THEIR QUOTAS TO CATCH,

02:46.333 --> 02:48.533
AND BETWEEN THEM
AND THE FINISH LINE,

02:48.533 --> 02:51.667
A 300-MILE-WIDE ARCTIC STORM.

02:51.667 --> 02:54.200
GOD BLESS YOU.
STAY SAFE.

02:54.200 --> 02:56.900
OKAY, LET'S KEEP IN TOUCH.
I'LL CALL YOU TOMORROW.

02:56.900 --> 03:00.533
ALL RIGHT. OKAY.
ALL RIGHT. OKAY, BYE.

03:06.333 --> 03:08.633
Johnathan:
ONE MORE TIME AROUND THE BLOCK.

03:08.633 --> 03:11.600
I GOT ONE TRIP LEFT
FOR THE REST OF MY LIFE.

03:11.600 --> 03:14.833
THE LAST TRIP THAT
I'M EVER GONNA DO.

03:14.833 --> 03:16.800
[ WIND WHISTLING ]

03:16.800 --> 03:19.100
THIS IS AS UGLY AS IT GETS.

03:21.433 --> 03:25.233
**

03:25.233 --> 03:26.933
Narrator:
BEFORE CAPTAIN JOHNATHAN

03:26.933 --> 03:30.200
CAN KICK OFF THE LAST TRIP
OF HIS STORIED CAREER...

03:30.200 --> 03:33.333
WE'VE TOOK ON ABOUT
45 TONS OF ICE.

03:33.333 --> 03:35.267
IT'S JUST MISERABLE.

03:35.267 --> 03:40.433
Narrator: ...
HE'S GOT 90,000 POUNDS OF ICE
THAT'S FOUND A HOME ON HIS BOAT.

03:40.433 --> 03:43.867
-[ SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY ]
-IT'S SERIOUSLY ICED UP.

03:45.067 --> 03:47.467
WE GOT MORE THAN WE
BARGAINED FOR RIGHT HERE.

03:50.800 --> 03:53.233
RIGHT NOW, WE'RE JUST GONNA
DRIFT AND PIT, YOU KNOW,

03:53.233 --> 03:55.867
START CHIPPING ICE
AS MUCH AS WE CAN.

03:55.867 --> 03:57.667
GONNA BE A LONG ONE.

04:05.633 --> 04:08.967
Johnathan:
IT'S A TOUGH WAY TO MAKE
A LIVING, THAT'S FOR DAMN SURE.

04:08.967 --> 04:11.800
ISN'T IT FUN OUT HERE?

04:11.800 --> 04:13.900
SO YOU WANNA BE A CRABBER?

04:13.900 --> 04:15.300
WHOA!

04:15.300 --> 04:18.333
MAMA DIDN'T TELL ME THERE
WAS GONNA BE DAYS LIKE THESE.

04:23.067 --> 04:25.567
WHOA.

04:30.067 --> 04:31.533
I'M OVER IT.

04:31.533 --> 04:34.533
37 YEARS OF PAIN AND "SUFFRAGE."

04:34.533 --> 04:36.367
YOU SEE ME BACK OUT HERE AGAIN,

04:36.367 --> 04:38.967
KICK ME RIGHT IN THE NUTS
AND GOUGE MY EYES OUT.

04:38.967 --> 04:41.167
I'LL DO IT MYSELF
WHEN WE COME OUT HERE AGAIN.

04:41.167 --> 04:43.967
I'LL KICK MYSELF IN MY OWN NUTS
AND POKE MY OWN EYE.

04:45.433 --> 04:47.867
OH, NO, IT AIN'T GOOD.

04:47.867 --> 04:51.133
GET THIS BOAT CLEARED,
GET THE ICE OFF

04:51.133 --> 04:55.133
SO WE FEEL A LITTLE BIT
LIGHTER, FEEL A LOT BETTER.

04:56.900 --> 04:58.967
Johnathan: I CAN'T WAIT TO PULL
THAT GEAR WE SET

04:58.967 --> 05:00.900
ON THE WAY
TO THE ISLAND HERE, THOUGH, MAN.

05:00.900 --> 05:04.500
I WENT RIGHT THROUGH
THREE SURVEYS THAT SHOWED CRAB,

05:04.500 --> 05:06.367
SO THE QUICKER WE GET THIS DONE,

05:06.367 --> 05:09.200
THE QUICKER WE'LL GO BACK
AND GET 'EM.

05:09.200 --> 05:11.300
Narrator:
JOHNATHAN HAS SET IN AN AREA

05:11.300 --> 05:15.700
WHERE THE SUMMER CRAB SURVEY
DETECTED A LARGE BIOMASS.

05:15.700 --> 05:17.633
WE'RE SO CLOSE, MAN.
I MEAN...

05:17.633 --> 05:19.867
[ SIGHS ]

05:19.867 --> 05:23.100
Narrator: BUT THE ICE IS KEEPING
THE CRAB FROM HIS TANKS.

05:23.100 --> 05:25.633
Johnathan:
THIS IS RIDICULOUS.

05:27.967 --> 05:31.567
WE CAN USE THE CRANE
TO PICK AND MOVE UP.

05:31.567 --> 05:34.800
I'M GONNA PUT MY SHOES ON. I'M
GONNA GET THAT FREESTANDING MAST

05:34.800 --> 05:36.700
'CAUSE I'M EXPERT MARKSMAN.

05:36.700 --> 05:38.400
-RIGHT THERE.
-ONE SHOT, ONE KILL.

05:38.400 --> 05:39.567
WATCH THIS [BLEEP]

05:39.567 --> 05:41.067
Narrator:
THROUGH THE YEARS...

05:41.067 --> 05:42.100
FIRE IN THE HOLE!

05:42.100 --> 05:44.233
[ GUNSHOTS ]

05:44.233 --> 05:47.700
...BREAKING ICE HAS BEEN A
JOHNATHAN HILLSTRAND SPECIALTY.

05:47.700 --> 05:49.900
STAY AWAY
AND DON'T COME BACK!

05:51.267 --> 05:53.067
I'M GONNA GET
MY HOODIE SHIRT ON.

05:53.067 --> 05:56.467
I'M GONNA GET MY BOOTS ON,
HELP THESE GUYS DE-ICE.

05:56.467 --> 05:58.567
I'M READY TO ROCK AND ROLL.

05:58.567 --> 06:01.733
Narrator: AND TODAY, HE REACHES
INTO HIS BAG OF TRICKS

06:01.733 --> 06:03.567
TO SPEED UP THE PROCESS.

06:05.933 --> 06:07.167
HEADS UP, GUYS.

06:10.100 --> 06:13.567
-YEAH, BABY!
-WHOO! WHOO!

06:13.567 --> 06:16.700
**

06:20.933 --> 06:22.367
[ DRILL WHIRS ]

06:23.967 --> 06:26.500
-HEADS UP, GUYS.
-HEADS UP.

06:28.500 --> 06:29.867
[ CHEERING ]

06:42.200 --> 06:43.867
YEAH!

06:43.867 --> 06:47.067
**

06:52.867 --> 06:56.400
JOHNNY IS BREAKING SOME ICE
OFF THE HOUSE RIGHT NOW

06:56.400 --> 06:58.967
IN A MAJOR WAY.

07:00.433 --> 07:02.767
HE'S BREAKING ICE IN BULK.

07:02.767 --> 07:04.233
[ LAUGHS ]

07:04.233 --> 07:07.433
**

07:11.933 --> 07:13.733
Johnathan:
HOLD ON HERE. [BLEEP]

07:13.733 --> 07:16.467
THESE ARE NOT
THE BOOTS TO WEAR.

07:16.467 --> 07:19.533
**

07:30.767 --> 07:32.833
Man: SOUTH WIND, 50 KNOTS.

07:32.833 --> 07:35.100
SEAS, 28 FEET.

07:35.100 --> 07:37.433
SCATTERED SNOW SHOWERS
IN THE EVENING.

07:39.833 --> 07:42.367
Narrator:
240 MILES SOUTHEAST...

07:49.067 --> 07:51.667
...ON THE 155-FOOT WIZARD.

07:51.667 --> 07:54.067
COME ON AROUND, GIRL.
COME ON.

07:56.100 --> 07:58.667
YOU GUYS JUST STAY HIDDEN UP
THERE FOR A MINUTE, OKAY?

07:58.667 --> 08:01.200
I GOTTA PUT HER
ON THE PORT SIDE OF THE DITCH.

08:03.733 --> 08:05.900
HANGING ON!

08:05.900 --> 08:08.933
**

08:08.933 --> 08:10.100
[ SIGHS ]

08:10.100 --> 08:13.400
BACK IN THE DITCH,
BACK IN THE SEAS.

08:13.400 --> 08:15.900
BACK IN THE STORM.

08:15.900 --> 08:17.967
WRITE A NEW NOVEL.

08:19.167 --> 08:23.067
"MY LIFE IN THE EYE
OF THE STORM" BY KEITH COLBURN.

08:23.067 --> 08:25.900
A SURVIVOR OF THE WINTERS
IN THE BERING SEA.

08:25.900 --> 08:29.600
**

08:29.600 --> 08:32.967
Narrator:
BROADSIDE TO 25-FOOT SEAS,

08:32.967 --> 08:37.567
CAPTAIN KEITH COLBURN FIGHTS HIS
WAY TO THE TOP OF HIS STRING.

08:37.567 --> 08:40.100
YOU KNOW WHAT? THIS IS
WHAT WE FISH IN OUT HERE.

08:40.100 --> 08:41.799
THIS IS THE BERING SEA.
IT'S WINTER.

08:41.799 --> 08:43.767
THIS IS WHAT
THE WEATHER IS.

08:43.767 --> 08:45.633
IT'S GETTING HARDER AND HARDER
EVERY YEAR

08:45.633 --> 08:47.100
TO MAKE
A BUCK OUT HERE.

08:47.100 --> 08:50.267
AND THIS YEAR, HARDER THAN ANY
I'VE EXPERIENCED IN MY CAREER.

08:50.267 --> 08:53.267
BATTLING STORMS AND BAD NUMBERS
THE ENTIRE WINTER SEASON...

08:53.267 --> 08:55.633
RIGHT NOW, WE'RE ON
SOME FRESH BOTTOM,

08:55.633 --> 08:59.133
AND I'M HOPING WE'LL POP
SOME DECENT COUNTS.

08:59.133 --> 09:03.667
...THE SKIPPER IS LOOKING TO
CHANGE HIS LUCK ON NEW GROUNDS.

09:03.667 --> 09:06.400
WE GOT ABOUT ANOTHER 50 POTS
TO HAUL AFTER THIS.

09:06.400 --> 09:10.567
WE SHOULD HAVE PROBABLY
70,000 TO 75,000 POUNDS.

09:13.867 --> 09:15.500
ALL RIGHT, GUYS,
HERE WE GO.

09:15.500 --> 09:17.733
ALL RIGHT,
LET'S CATCH SOME CRAB.

09:17.733 --> 09:19.700
THE FIRST ONE'S
COMING UP.

09:30.067 --> 09:32.367
ROLL THE OLD DOG ON THIS ONE.

09:32.367 --> 09:34.067
WHOA, WHOA,
WHOA, WHOA, WHOA.

09:36.733 --> 09:40.433
NO, NO, NO, NO, NO.

09:40.433 --> 09:43.300
COMING DOWN THE RAIL.
A LITTLE SLURPER.

09:53.067 --> 09:55.267
MIGHT TAKE A WAVE OR TWO
HERE DURING THIS HAUL.

09:57.100 --> 10:01.200
EAT YOUR CANDY BARS
OR YOUR LITTLE PROTEIN PACKS.

10:01.200 --> 10:03.067
THIS COULD BE A LONG DAY.

10:05.367 --> 10:06.867
COME ON, CRAB.

10:08.533 --> 10:10.933
LET'S SEE WHAT WE GOT HERE.
COME ON.

10:17.233 --> 10:19.300
WHOO! YEAH, BABY!

10:19.300 --> 10:22.433
THERE'S A GOOD FIRST POT
FOR THE LAST PICK.

10:22.433 --> 10:25.033
-[BLEEP] YEAH!
-POW, POW!

10:37.133 --> 10:39.733
3-5-5.

10:39.733 --> 10:41.067
355, RIGHT ON.

10:41.067 --> 10:43.700
IT'S LOOKING GOOD.

10:43.700 --> 10:47.033
FIRST POT
HAD 355 CRAB IN IT.

10:47.033 --> 10:49.333
I'M HOPING WE CAN SEE
THAT THROUGH THE STRING.

10:49.333 --> 10:51.533
IF WE DO, THAT'S PRETTY MUCH
THE TICKET

10:51.533 --> 10:52.933
TO GETTING THIS BOAT FULL

10:52.933 --> 10:54.400
AND GETTING THIS
SEASON OVER WITH.

10:54.400 --> 10:55.867
AND THERE ISN'T A GUY
ON THIS BOAT

10:55.867 --> 10:57.300
THAT DOESN'T WANT
THAT TO HAPPEN.

10:57.300 --> 10:58.633
YEAH.

10:58.633 --> 11:00.233
[BLEEP] YEAH.

11:00.233 --> 11:03.367
GO AHEAD AND COUNT FOR ME,
WILL YOU, GUYS?

11:08.933 --> 11:12.300
**

11:13.100 --> 11:14.867
WATCH OUT, WATCH OUT!

11:16.067 --> 11:17.600
WHOA!

11:17.600 --> 11:19.267
HANG ON, HANG ON,
HANG ON!

11:19.267 --> 11:20.400
AAH!

11:25.600 --> 11:26.867
Man: YEAH!

11:26.867 --> 11:28.467
[BLEEP] YEAH!

11:28.467 --> 11:30.933
GO AHEAD AND COUNT
FOR ME, WILL YOU, GUYS?

11:30.933 --> 11:32.933
Narrator: ON THE WIZARD...

11:36.733 --> 11:39.800
WATCH OUT, WATCH OUT!

11:39.800 --> 11:41.367
WHOA.

11:41.367 --> 11:43.200
HANG ON,
HANG ON, HANG ON!

11:43.200 --> 11:44.267
AAH!

11:45.633 --> 11:47.067
YOU OKAY?

11:49.300 --> 11:52.100
OH [BLEEP] ME.

11:52.100 --> 11:54.400
AAH.

11:54.400 --> 11:56.933
SORRY ABOUT THAT, GUYS.

11:56.933 --> 11:59.267
I GOT DISTRACTED.

12:00.333 --> 12:03.067
OH!

12:03.067 --> 12:04.633
THAT WAS A BIG ONE.

12:04.633 --> 12:08.500
WE JUST TOOK A BIG,
BIG GREEN ONE OVER THE RAIL.

12:09.833 --> 12:11.867
IT CLIPPED CROSBY
PRETTY GOOD.

12:14.067 --> 12:16.367
AAH!

12:16.367 --> 12:20.200
YOU ALWAYS LOVE IT WHEN WAVES
COME OUT OF THE BACK SIDE.

12:25.833 --> 12:28.300
WE'RE ALL GOOD, SO I'M GOOD.

12:28.300 --> 12:30.900
I CAN'T BE LOOKING 100%
OF THE TIME DOWN THERE.

12:30.900 --> 12:33.767
I'VE GOT THE RADAR TO LOOK,
I'VE GOT THE PLOTTER.

12:33.767 --> 12:35.933
I'VE GOT ALL THIS
BOOKKEEPING I GOT TO DO.

12:35.933 --> 12:37.600
I GOTTA MULTITASK,

12:37.600 --> 12:39.633
AND ONCE I THINK THE GUYS
ARE GOOD AND SAFE,

12:39.633 --> 12:41.433
I'LL GO TO THIS,
BUT JUST ALL OF A SUDDEN,

12:41.433 --> 12:43.467
OUT OF THE CORNER
OF MY EYE, BANG.

12:43.467 --> 12:45.500
ONE REAL BIG WAVE.

12:45.500 --> 12:47.967
IT'S HARD TO FOCUS ON THAT
WHEN YOU GOT A TASK TO DO.

12:47.967 --> 12:49.333
WHOOPS.

12:49.333 --> 12:52.167
YOU'RE KIND OF RELYING
ON YOUR CAPTAIN UP THERE,

12:52.167 --> 12:54.300
AND IF HE'S NOT COMPLETELY
PAYING ATTENTION,

12:54.300 --> 12:57.733
WELL, YOU COULD BE SWIMMING.

12:57.733 --> 13:01.400
SO NOW IT'S TIME TO
REALLY PAY ATTENTION HERE.

13:01.400 --> 13:04.100
GOTTA DO MY BEST NOT TO
TAKE ANOTHER ONE OF THOSE.

13:10.333 --> 13:12.733
Narrator:
240 MILES NORTHWEST...

13:17.600 --> 13:19.067
...ON THE TIME BANDIT.

13:19.067 --> 13:21.433
Johnathan: ALL RIGHT, MAN,
WE'RE BACK IN BUSINESS.

13:21.433 --> 13:24.767
THIS CRAZY WEATHER.
WE GOT SOUTHEAST 25.

13:27.133 --> 13:29.167
31-FOOT SEAS.

13:29.167 --> 13:32.100
ICE IS JUST SHEDDING
OFF THIS BOAT, MAN.

13:32.100 --> 13:35.300
JUST TURNED BACK
INTO BLACK BOAT.

13:35.300 --> 13:37.667
GOOD OLD TIME BANDIT,
BACK IN BLACK.

13:37.667 --> 13:40.967
AFTER CLEARING
HIS VESSEL OF ICE...

13:40.967 --> 13:43.767
[ SIGHS ]
MY LAST [BLEEP] SEASON.

13:43.767 --> 13:46.300
I CAN'T WAIT TO GET HOME!

13:46.300 --> 13:50.533
...CAPTAIN JOHNATHAN HILLSTRAND
LOOKS FOR ONE LAST MONSTER HAUL

13:50.533 --> 13:52.100
TO END HIS CAREER.

13:52.100 --> 13:55.200
I HAIL MARY'D THE DAMN SURVEY
BY ST. MATTHEW ISLAND.

13:55.200 --> 13:58.800
NEVER DONE THIS BEFORE,
BUT IT'S MY LAST SEASON.

13:58.800 --> 14:03.267
HEY, I GOTTA KNOW WHERE THE HELL
THESE CRAB ARE, YOU KNOW?

14:03.267 --> 14:05.133
THIS DAMN SURVEY HERE SAYS

14:05.133 --> 14:06.967
THERE'S 10 MILLION
POUNDS UP HERE.

14:09.133 --> 14:12.233
SO I SET UP THROUGH THESE
THREE SURVEYS RIGHT HERE.

14:12.233 --> 14:13.467
WE'LL SEE WHAT'S HERE.

14:13.467 --> 14:15.967
THERE'S GOTTA BE
SOME KIND OF SIGNS OF LIFE.

14:15.967 --> 14:18.167
OR THE SURVEY'S
FULL OF [BLEEP]

14:18.167 --> 14:22.267
WORKING OFF ALASKA FISH AND
GAME'S CRAB POPULATION SURVEY,

14:22.267 --> 14:26.200
JOHNATHAN GAMBLED HIS RETIREMENT
SET ON UNFAMILIAR WATERS

14:26.200 --> 14:29.367
JUST 130 MILES OFF
ST. MATTHEW ISLAND.

14:29.367 --> 14:32.500
BURN THE CANDLE,
BURN THE JESUS CANDLE.

14:32.500 --> 14:33.767
KNOCK ON WOOD.

14:33.767 --> 14:36.067
DON'T KNOW HOW MANY TIMES
I KNOCKED ON WOOD TODAY.

14:36.067 --> 14:39.933
HE'S BETTING THAT HIS TICKET
TO RETIREMENT LIES BENEATH.

14:39.933 --> 14:42.833
MY CURIOSITY WANT TO KNOW
WHAT THE HECK'S OVER HERE,

14:42.833 --> 14:45.500
AND I'M GONNA
FIND OUT RIGHT NOW,

14:45.500 --> 14:47.200
WHAT KIND OF LIFE'S
DOWN HERE.

14:51.467 --> 14:54.900
SURVEY SAYS...THIS WHOLE AREA
THAT WE'RE FISHING IN

14:54.900 --> 14:56.333
IS GONNA BE A HONEY POT.

14:56.333 --> 14:59.100
WE'RE GONNA CHILL IT, BOY.
WE'RE GONNA CHILL IT.

14:59.100 --> 15:00.300
YEAH, BABY!

15:05.533 --> 15:07.833
COME ON, CRABS,
GIVE IT UP!

15:12.067 --> 15:13.867
WAAH-WAAH.

15:13.867 --> 15:16.233
WE DON'T WANT THIS POT.

15:16.233 --> 15:18.867
DOESN'T LOOK LIKE
THERE'S ANYBODY HOME.

15:18.867 --> 15:20.700
AAH!

15:20.700 --> 15:22.567
BOO!

15:22.567 --> 15:24.767
I WAS HOPING THAT WAS
GONNA BE ABOUT HALF FULL.

15:24.767 --> 15:30.067
OR AT LEAST HAVE 150
OR 120 OR 250.

15:30.067 --> 15:31.467
NEXT!

15:40.633 --> 15:42.467
[BLEEP]
SONS OF BITCHES.

15:46.067 --> 15:47.800
LOOKING [BLEEP]

15:47.800 --> 15:51.700
I'M JUST CURIOUS TO WHERE
THE [BLEEP] THOSE CRAB ARE

15:51.700 --> 15:53.300
ON THIS SURVEY.

15:53.300 --> 15:55.267
UH-OH. UH-OH.

15:55.267 --> 15:57.500
[BLEEP]

15:57.500 --> 15:59.667
I DID A SURVEY,

15:59.667 --> 16:03.133
AND THIS SURVEY
DON'T MATCH MY [BLEEP] SURVEY.

16:03.133 --> 16:05.867
SURVEY SAYS --
YOU KNOW WHAT?

16:05.867 --> 16:08.067
THIS IS THE LAST TIME
I'M EVER GONNA HAVE TO

16:08.067 --> 16:09.267
LOOK AT A SURVEY ANYWAY.

16:09.267 --> 16:10.967
[BLEEP]

16:10.967 --> 16:12.733
OH, NOT AGAIN.

16:12.733 --> 16:15.300
Narrator: WITH EACH EMPTY POT
THAT COMES ABOARD,

16:15.300 --> 16:18.200
JOHNATHAN'S DREAM
OF A BIG FINISH LOOKS,

16:18.200 --> 16:20.333
WELL, LIKE A DREAM.

16:20.333 --> 16:23.467
THAT'S MY SURVEY.
MY SURVEY SAYS [BLEEP] YOU.

16:32.700 --> 16:35.500
THAT SURVEY STRING
WAS A BIG WASTE OF OUR TIME.

16:35.500 --> 16:38.233
SURVEY SAYS NOTHING!

16:38.233 --> 16:39.533
NADA!

16:39.533 --> 16:42.067
WOW, THAT'S JUST
DISAPPOINTING.

16:42.067 --> 16:43.967
THERE'S SUPPOSED TO BE
10 MILLION POUNDS

16:43.967 --> 16:45.333
UP HERE SOMEWHERE.

16:45.333 --> 16:47.700
I AM NOT SEEING IT.

16:47.700 --> 16:50.333
THIS THING'S WORTHLESS.

16:50.333 --> 16:52.300
WORTHLESS INFORMATION.

16:53.967 --> 16:56.800
[BLEEP] THIS THING.
PIECE OF [BLEEP]

17:00.167 --> 17:02.933
Narrator: THE SKIPPER VENTS
HIS FRUSTRATION...

17:02.933 --> 17:05.700
THERE'S THE [BLEEP]
SURVEY FOR YOU.

17:05.700 --> 17:08.967
...IN CLASSIC HILLSTRAND
FASHION.

17:12.666 --> 17:15.333
...THAT SURVEY AND
SHOVE IT UP YOUR ASS.

17:15.333 --> 17:17.067
[BLEEP] THAT SURVEY.

17:17.067 --> 17:19.200
**

17:19.200 --> 17:20.467
WOULDN'T BE THE FIRST TIME

17:20.467 --> 17:23.300
JOHNATHAN HAD AN ISSUE
WITH THE GOVERNMENT.

17:23.300 --> 17:26.200
MIGHT AS WELL TAKE THE SHIRT
OFF MY [BLEEP] BACK!

17:26.200 --> 17:29.167
HERE, YOU WANT THIS?
TAKE THAT, TOO!

17:29.167 --> 17:32.233
[ SHOUTING INDISTINCTLY ]

17:32.233 --> 17:35.067
...OR A PIECE OF EQUIPMENT.

17:35.067 --> 17:36.767
CAN'T USE THAT
ON MY BOAT!

17:36.767 --> 17:40.367
[BLEEP]
IT'S ALL YOUR FAULT!

17:40.367 --> 17:42.467
...OR ANYTHING,
FOR THAT MATTER.

17:43.967 --> 17:46.400
[BLEEP] SKATEBOARD'S
[BLEEP] OFF THE BOAT.

17:46.400 --> 17:48.500
[ EXPLOSION ]
-OH!

17:48.500 --> 17:49.533
[ EXPLOSION ]

17:49.533 --> 17:50.967
WOW!

17:50.967 --> 17:53.267
WHOO!

17:53.267 --> 17:54.600
HOLY [BLEEP]

17:54.600 --> 17:56.767
[BLEEP] SURVEY CAN
[BLEEP] ITSELF.

18:03.400 --> 18:05.433
TAKING CARE OF THAT.
YEAH, NEAL'S BURNING IT.

18:05.433 --> 18:07.133
HE'S BURNING THAT
SON OF A BITCH.

18:08.833 --> 18:12.300
JUST IN THE NICK OF FIRE.

18:12.300 --> 18:14.667
GET IT, NEAL, GET IT!
GET THAT SON OF A BITCH.

18:16.600 --> 18:18.700
[BLEEP] THAT [BLEEP]

18:18.700 --> 18:20.767
[BLEEP] THAT SURVEY.

18:20.767 --> 18:22.067
THAT SURVEY, MAN, SAYS --

18:22.067 --> 18:24.067
SURVEY SAYS [BLEEP]

18:24.067 --> 18:25.500
BEAUTIFUL.

18:27.567 --> 18:29.733
CURIOSITY SOMETIMES
KILLED THE CAT.

18:29.733 --> 18:31.967
YOU KNOW WHAT I'M SAYING?

18:31.967 --> 18:34.733
TIME FOR MY FALLBACK PLAN.

18:36.767 --> 18:38.900
Narrator:
IN NEED OF A NEW HOME...

18:38.900 --> 18:41.733
I'VE DONE A LOT OF SEASONS.

18:41.733 --> 18:43.667
A SEASONED VETERAN.

18:43.667 --> 18:45.567
...JOHNATHAN TAKES
ADVANTAGE OF INTEL

18:45.567 --> 18:48.967
HE'S AMASSED IN ALMOST FOUR
DECADES ON THE BERING SEA.

18:48.967 --> 18:52.267
THERE'S AN AREA OVER HERE
IN THIS NICE LITTLE GUT HERE.

18:52.267 --> 18:53.733
THAT'S WHERE
WE USED TO FISH.

18:53.733 --> 18:55.833
THAT CANYON USED
TO PRODUCE SOME CRAB,

18:55.833 --> 19:00.100
SO 37 YEARS,
BACK TO THE CANYON.

19:01.133 --> 19:03.300
GO BACK TO MY LITTLE SPOT.

19:03.300 --> 19:06.700
I'M JUST GONNA GO THERE
AND DIG IN LIKE A TICK

19:06.700 --> 19:09.900
AND HOPE THEY DON'T RUN
OUT OF CRAB RIGHT THERE.

19:11.067 --> 19:12.367
STACK 'ER.

19:12.367 --> 19:13.667
HEADS UP!

19:15.400 --> 19:17.067
IT COMES DOWN TO THIS.

19:17.067 --> 19:21.367
LAST CHANCE FOR...

19:21.367 --> 19:23.400
GREATNESS.

19:23.400 --> 19:26.867
**

19:33.267 --> 19:36.200
Narrator:
520 MILES FROM DUTCH HARBOR

19:36.200 --> 19:38.200
ON THE TIME BANDIT...

19:41.133 --> 19:43.233
SET ANOTHER ONE RIGHT HERE.

19:45.600 --> 19:47.500
GOING OVER.

19:49.367 --> 19:52.933
I'M GONNA GET MY SET DONE,
OUR ESCAPE PLAN.

19:52.933 --> 19:54.067
YEAH, BABY!

19:54.067 --> 19:55.833
AFTER STRIKING OUT
ON THE SURVEY SET,

19:55.833 --> 20:00.200
CAPTAIN JOHNATHAN HILLSTRAND
HEADS SOUTH TO FRESH GROUNDS...

20:00.200 --> 20:01.700
HANG ON, GUYS.

20:01.700 --> 20:02.733
[BLEEP]

20:02.733 --> 20:05.133
WATCH OUT.

20:05.133 --> 20:09.067
Narrator: ...AND INTO THE GRIP
OF A BERING SEA SQUALL.

20:09.067 --> 20:10.933
JUST, NO ONE GET HURT.

20:14.900 --> 20:16.533
GOING OVER.

20:18.167 --> 20:19.467
THIS WIND JUST CAME UP.

20:19.467 --> 20:21.533
IT'S BLOWING
IN THE WRONG DIRECTION.

20:21.533 --> 20:23.467
IT'S SUPPOSED TO BLOW
SOUTHEAST.

20:23.467 --> 20:26.267
IT'S BLOWING NORTHWEST.

20:26.267 --> 20:30.367
THE WEATHER CAME UP,
SNEAKING UP ON US.

20:36.200 --> 20:37.400
WHOA!

20:37.400 --> 20:41.033
SINK OR SWIM, BABY!
WHOO!

20:41.033 --> 20:43.600
YEP. I WANT TO
GET OUTTA HERE.

20:43.600 --> 20:46.700
I'M NOT COMING OUT
ON THIS RODEO RIDE NO MORE.

20:48.033 --> 20:50.400
TIRED OF BEING
IN THIS WASHING MACHINE.

20:50.400 --> 20:52.333
I'M GONNA FINISH THIS TRIP

20:52.333 --> 20:55.600
AND BE AS HAPPY A SON OF
A BITCH TO BE GOING IN.

21:00.167 --> 21:04.467
I SET, LIKE, 80-MILE STRING UP
HERE OUT IN THE DEEP GUT.

21:04.467 --> 21:07.367
IT'S USUALLY WHERE
THEY LOVE TO HANG.

21:07.367 --> 21:10.367
THIS FROM HERE TO HERE
THE LAST 25 YEARS.

21:10.367 --> 21:12.433
BRINGS BACK
A LOT OF MEMORIES.

21:12.433 --> 21:14.800
GOING OVER.

21:14.800 --> 21:17.233
HOPEFULLY, WE GOT
THE NUMBERS WE NEED.

21:17.233 --> 21:19.167
WE DON'T FALL
ON OUR FACES.

21:19.167 --> 21:21.933
Narrator: STILL SHORT OF HIS
RETIREMENT QUOTA...

21:21.933 --> 21:24.600
IT'S NEVER A FISHER
THING, EVER, EVER.

21:24.600 --> 21:27.167
...THE SKIPPER IS BANKING
ON A FORMER HONEY HOLE

21:27.167 --> 21:29.633
TO DELIVER HIS REMAINING POUNDS.

21:29.633 --> 21:32.800
ONE MORE CHANCE.
RIGHT HERE, THIS IS IT.

21:32.800 --> 21:34.533
OKAY, GUYS,
THIS IS THE LAST ONE.

21:34.533 --> 21:35.700
WE'RE GOING OVER.

21:35.700 --> 21:37.767
WHOO!

21:39.167 --> 21:40.400
LAST ONE!

21:40.400 --> 21:41.933
COME BACK LOADED!

21:41.933 --> 21:43.333
LAST ONE SET!

21:46.133 --> 21:48.067
WE'RE GONNA FIGHT
TILL THE BITTER END,

21:48.067 --> 21:50.500
TRYING TO FIND
THE MOTHER LODE.

21:50.500 --> 21:54.233
THIS IS HOW FAR WE'VE COME.
THIS IS HOW FAR I GOTTA GO.

21:54.233 --> 21:58.833
RAIN AND SLEET,
SNOW, 40-FOOT WAVES.

21:58.833 --> 22:00.900
AIN'T NO ONE STOPPING ME NOW.

22:03.233 --> 22:05.433
MAILMAN'S COMING!

22:08.767 --> 22:13.733
Narrator: 240 MILES SOUTHEAST
ON THE WIZARD...

22:16.133 --> 22:18.500
[ BOAT CREAKING ]

22:18.500 --> 22:20.067
[ HORN BLARES ]

22:21.867 --> 22:25.733
Keith: WE'RE FISHING IN
BERING SEA WEATHER AGAIN.

22:25.733 --> 22:28.900
CRAPPY, BAD VISIBILITY,

22:28.900 --> 22:32.167
BIG WAVES, BLOWING SNOW.

22:32.167 --> 22:35.300
[ SIGHS ]

22:35.300 --> 22:38.067
WIZARD WEATHER.

22:38.067 --> 22:42.233
Narrator:
CAPTAIN KEITH COLBURN'S FISHING
HAS BEEN PLAGUED BY HEAVY SEAS.

22:42.233 --> 22:44.267
Keith: THIS STRING'S ONE
OF THE TWO STRINGS

22:44.267 --> 22:46.167
WE LEFT TO THE EAST OF OUR GEAR,

22:46.167 --> 22:49.267
RIGHT WHERE WE HAD REALLY GOOD
FISHING ON OUR OPENING PICK.

22:49.267 --> 22:52.067
AND IF WE CAN DIG 200 CRAB
PER POT OUT OF THESE POTS,

22:52.067 --> 22:54.900
I'M GONNA BE -- I WILL BE VERY,
VERY HAPPY WITH THAT.

22:54.900 --> 22:56.933
Narrator: A GOOD HAUL WILL
GIVE THE VETERAN

22:56.933 --> 23:00.067
THE NUMBERS HE NEEDS
TO END HIS SEASON.

23:00.067 --> 23:02.200
WE'LL SEE. HOPEFULLY WE GET
SOME CRAB IN THIS

23:02.200 --> 23:05.533
SO WE DON'T HAVE TO
PICK UP AND TRAVEL.

23:07.067 --> 23:08.267
Keith: ALL RIGHT, GUYS.

23:12.200 --> 23:15.433
...SUCKS, SO JUST STAY SHARP
AT THE RAIL, OKAY?

23:15.433 --> 23:16.967
OH!

23:18.233 --> 23:21.733
[ LINE WHIPS ]

23:21.733 --> 23:24.200
WILD WEATHER'S PICKING UP.

23:24.200 --> 23:26.200
BAGS ARE COMING UP BACKWARDS.

23:26.200 --> 23:28.700
WE GOT A WHOLE LIST OF STUFF
THAT'S GOING ON RIGHT NOW.

23:28.700 --> 23:32.633
CURRENT'S RUNNING THROUGH HERE
KIND OF EAST AND WEST.

23:32.633 --> 23:35.367
WHEN THE CONDITIONS
ARE JUST RIGHT,

23:35.367 --> 23:37.933
IT'S ALMOST IMPOSSIBLE
TO GET THAT BUOY IN.

23:37.933 --> 23:40.767
Narrator: THE BERING SEA ISN'T
WILLING TO GIVE UP ITS BOUNTY

23:40.767 --> 23:42.067
WITHOUT A FIGHT.

23:42.067 --> 23:44.933
GONNA BE A PAIN IN THE BUTT
TO HAUL THIS GEAR.

23:44.933 --> 23:48.733
Narrator:
STRONG OCEAN CURRENTS GENERATE
IMMENSE DOWNWARD PRESSURE

23:48.733 --> 23:50.133
ON THE POTS.

23:51.467 --> 23:53.467
[ LINE SNAPS ]
-OH [BLEEP]

23:53.467 --> 23:55.233
Keith: OH, COME ON,
GET IT OVER THE RAIL, GUYS.

23:55.233 --> 23:56.467
COME ON,
COME ON, COME ON!

23:56.467 --> 23:58.067
WATCH YOUR FEET,
WATCH YOUR FEET!

23:58.067 --> 23:59.833
GOTTA BE [BLEEP]
KIDDING ME!

23:59.833 --> 24:01.567
HE'S GOT IT, HE'S GOT IT.

24:06.633 --> 24:08.067
AAH!

24:08.067 --> 24:10.933
WATCH YOUR FEET NOW!
YOU'RE ALL IN IT!

24:15.233 --> 24:18.633
WHOA, WHOA, WHOA!
HOLY [BLEEP]

24:18.633 --> 24:20.767
[BLEEP]

24:28.733 --> 24:31.067
THAT'S A BIG MAN
TO GET TOWED ACROSS DECK

24:31.067 --> 24:32.733
BY A SET OF
[BLEEP] BAGS.

24:32.733 --> 24:35.300
I HAVEN'T BEEN ZIPPED
ACROSS DECK LIKE THAT

24:35.300 --> 24:37.700
WITHOUT A WAVE BEING INVOLVED.

24:37.700 --> 24:39.200
Keith: THE THING IS THIS.

24:39.200 --> 24:42.267
IF CROSBY'S TANGLED UP
AND GOES WITH THAT BUOY,

24:42.267 --> 24:46.933
HE GOES AROUND THAT BLOCK,
OVER THE SIDE,

24:46.933 --> 24:49.967
UNDER THE BOAT,
AND INTO THE STIR.

24:49.967 --> 24:51.067
NO MORE CROSBY.

24:51.067 --> 24:53.533
KIND OF [BLEEP]
SCARY, MAN.

24:53.533 --> 24:55.933
Narrator:
BATTLING FIERCE TIDES...

24:55.933 --> 24:57.600
ALL RIGHT,
COMING AT YOU.

24:57.600 --> 25:00.800
...THE CREW MANAGES
TO MUSCLE THROUGH.

25:00.800 --> 25:03.233
STAY SHARP.

25:03.233 --> 25:05.067
OH [BLEEP] THERE GO
THE BUOYS AGAIN.

25:05.067 --> 25:07.500
[BLEEP]

25:07.500 --> 25:10.067
THERE WE GO, GET 'EM IN.

25:10.067 --> 25:13.533
**

25:13.533 --> 25:15.167
COME ON! GET ME
A POT OF CRAB.

25:15.167 --> 25:17.767
WELL, IT'S GOT SOMETHING IN IT,
I'M NOT SURE WHAT.

25:21.633 --> 25:24.167
COME ON, MAN. COME ON,
GIVE ME A GOOD COUNT.

25:24.167 --> 25:25.633
GIVE ME A GOOD COUNT.

25:28.067 --> 25:30.567
3-2-0.

25:30.567 --> 25:31.567
320, RIGHT ON!

25:31.567 --> 25:33.633
NICE CRAB?

25:33.633 --> 25:35.067
OH, YEAH.

25:35.067 --> 25:37.833
BIG CRAB. BIG CRAB.

25:37.833 --> 25:40.333
OOH! OOH! OOH!

25:43.067 --> 25:46.200
**

25:46.200 --> 25:48.800
I HOPE THEY'RE GONNA BE
A LITTLE EASIER TO HAUL.

25:48.800 --> 25:52.167
TAKE 'ER EASY NOW!
STOP DOING [BLEEP]

25:52.167 --> 25:54.967
NAH, THEY'RE NOT GONNA
BE ANY EASIER TO HAUL.

25:58.600 --> 26:01.433
I'LL BE A HAPPY GUY WHEN WE GET
THIS STRING OVER WITH.

26:01.433 --> 26:04.600
OH, CLEAN CRAB!
OH, COME HERE!

26:04.600 --> 26:06.900
-CLEAN!
-COME ON, BABY!

26:10.267 --> 26:12.867
-OH [BLEEP]
-PEOPLE, PULL, PULL, PULL!

26:15.933 --> 26:17.900
THAT IS EXACTLY
WHAT WE NEEDED.

26:17.900 --> 26:20.067
OH, DADDY!

26:20.067 --> 26:24.433
EVERY PASSING POT,
ONE POT CLOSER TO GOING HOME.

26:24.433 --> 26:26.567
355, RIGHT ON.

26:26.567 --> 26:27.767
THAT'LL WORK.

26:27.767 --> 26:29.867
ALL CLEAN CRAB!

26:34.733 --> 26:37.133
UNH, UNH, UNH!

26:37.133 --> 26:40.200
**

26:43.300 --> 26:44.633
POW.

26:48.867 --> 26:53.500
THE POT THEY JUST COUNTED
HAD 435 KEEPERS IN IT.

26:53.500 --> 26:56.067
THIS RIGHT HERE
SHOULD BE 200 PLUS.

26:56.067 --> 26:57.467
250s THROUGH ALL THAT.

26:57.467 --> 27:00.433
I THINK WE'RE GONNA START
PUTTING A BIG STACK ON.

27:00.433 --> 27:02.500
THAT'S IT, GUYS.
[ SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY ]

27:02.500 --> 27:04.867
GOOD JOB.
-PUT THE HAPPY SOCK ON!

27:04.867 --> 27:07.467
TIME TO GO!
-WHOO-HOO-HOO-HOO!

27:07.467 --> 27:10.900
I'M BREATHING A HUGE SIGH
OF RELIEF RIGHT NOW.

27:10.900 --> 27:13.933
WE STARTED AWFULLY SLOW,
WORST TRIP OF MY CAREER.

27:13.933 --> 27:16.800
THEY ALWAYS SAY, IT'S NOT HOW
YOU START, IT'S HOW YOU FINISH.

27:16.800 --> 27:19.400
WELL, YOU KNOW WHAT?
WE FINISHED STRONG.

27:19.400 --> 27:21.867
Narrator: AFTER SIX WEEKS
OF DANGEROUS WEATHER...

27:21.867 --> 27:23.900
-WHOO!
-...AND SPOTTY FISHING...

27:23.900 --> 27:27.433
IT WAS A SKINNY SEASON,
BUT IT WAS A SUCCESSFUL SEASON.

27:27.433 --> 27:31.933
...THE VETERAN SKIPPER HAS
HAULED 434,000 POUNDS OF CRAB

27:31.933 --> 27:35.167
FOR A TOTAL OF $1.7 MILLION,

27:35.167 --> 27:39.300
AND HIS CREW
WILL POCKET 54 GRAND EACH.

27:39.300 --> 27:41.800
IT'S A LOT TOUGHER
TO BE A BOAT OWNER TODAY

27:41.800 --> 27:44.567
THAN IT WAS
25, 30 YEARS AGO.

27:44.567 --> 27:46.200
THE FISHERIES
ARE DOWN RIGHT NOW,

27:46.200 --> 27:49.067
AND YOU REALLY HAVE
NO MARGIN FOR ERROR.

27:49.067 --> 27:51.333
YOU'VE GOTTA COME OUT HERE,
CATCH YOUR CRAB QUICK,

27:51.333 --> 27:52.867
KEEP YOUR COSTS DOWN,

27:52.867 --> 27:56.667
AND THAT'S THE ONLY WAY
YOU'RE GONNA SUCCEED.

27:56.667 --> 27:59.133
AND FORESEEING THE FUTURE
OF THIS FISHERY

27:59.133 --> 28:01.733
IS REALLY DIFFICULT.

28:01.733 --> 28:05.133
BUT I'LL TELL YOU WHAT, THIS
BOAT'LL BE FISHING NEXT YEAR.

28:14.233 --> 28:16.467
Narrator:
ON THE FISHING GROUNDS...

28:16.467 --> 28:19.100
I JUST CANNOT BELIEVE
THAT YOU ARE RETIRING, SO...

28:19.100 --> 28:20.567
[ LAUGHS ]

28:20.567 --> 28:23.467
WE'LL GET YOU ON SOME
WATER SKIS OR SOMETHING.

28:23.467 --> 28:24.967
SEE THE OTHER SIDE OF JOHN.

28:24.967 --> 28:27.233
WE HAVEN'T SEEN HOW YOU LOOK
IN SWIM TRUNKS YET.

28:27.233 --> 28:30.367
THAT'LL BE FUN.
[ LAUGHS ]

28:30.367 --> 28:34.567
Narrator: CAPTAIN SIG HANSEN
CATCHES UP WITH AN OLD BUDDY.

28:34.567 --> 28:37.633
OH, YEAH, THAT'LL BE SCARY.
THESE LEGS HAVEN'T SEEN THE SUN.

28:37.633 --> 28:39.467
THEY'LL BLIND YOU,
THEY'RE SO WHITE.

28:39.467 --> 28:40.700
[ LAUGHS ]

28:40.700 --> 28:43.267
THEY'RE SKINNY
LIKE PELICAN LEGS.

28:43.267 --> 28:44.967
[ LAUGHS ] BUT YOU KNOW,

28:44.967 --> 28:46.500
I SUPPOSE
IT'S LIKE ANYTHING ELSE.

28:46.500 --> 28:49.167
YOU KNOW WHEN YOU KNOW, RIGHT?
YOU KNOW IT IN YOUR HEART.

28:49.167 --> 28:51.367
IF YOU KNOW IT,
THEN IT'S THE RIGHT THING.

28:51.367 --> 28:53.233
YEAH.

28:53.233 --> 28:57.533
DON'T GET TOO COCKY,
BUT I NEED TO FINISH THIS TRIP,

28:57.533 --> 29:00.267
'CAUSE I CAN'T WAIT FOR IT
TO BE THE LAST TRIP

29:00.267 --> 29:02.600
I'LL EVER FISH
THIS CRAB AGAIN.

29:02.600 --> 29:04.167
[ LAUGHS ]

29:04.167 --> 29:07.700
THAT'S HOW SERIOUS I AM.

29:07.700 --> 29:09.600
UNREAL.

29:09.600 --> 29:11.067
ANYWAY, ALL RIGHT, MAN.

29:11.067 --> 29:13.300
WELL, WE GOTTA
GET GOING HERE.

29:13.300 --> 29:14.800
OKAY, MAN. GOOD LUCK.

29:14.800 --> 29:17.367
BYE, JOHNNY.
IT WAS GOOD TALKING TO YOU.

29:17.367 --> 29:19.600
WE'LL SEE YOU DOWN SOUTH.
I'M OUT.

29:19.600 --> 29:21.100
THANKS.

29:24.267 --> 29:27.067
UNREAL. JOHN'S RETIRING.

29:27.067 --> 29:30.833
AND I JUST DON'T KNOW
IF I COULD DO IT RIGHT NOW,

29:30.833 --> 29:32.333
BUT GOOD FOR JOHN.

29:32.333 --> 29:34.867
HE KNOWS IT WHEN HE KNOWS IT.

29:37.533 --> 29:39.433
Johnathan:
THAT'S WHY I'M GETTING OUT.

29:39.433 --> 29:42.067
I DON'T --
I DON'T NEED THE STRESS,

29:42.067 --> 29:44.400
AND I DON'T NEED THIS PRESSURE.

29:44.400 --> 29:47.500
OKAY, GUYS.
DON'T GET HURT.

29:47.500 --> 29:50.167
THIS WEATHER'S SUPPOSED TO BE
NORTH 20 THIS WHOLE SEASON,

29:50.167 --> 29:52.067
IN YOUR [BLEEP] FACE.

29:54.467 --> 29:57.067
YEAH, BABY! LET'S DO IT!

29:57.067 --> 29:58.400
Man: LET'S DO IT!

29:58.400 --> 30:00.567
Narrator:
CAPTAIN JOHNATHAN IS BANKING

30:00.567 --> 30:03.400
THAT THIS STRING WILL BE
THE LAST ONE OF HIS SEASON.

30:03.400 --> 30:07.967
I SET ACROSS THIS CANYON.
I'M GOING OUT ON TOP.

30:07.967 --> 30:09.567
LIKE A CHAMPION, HOPEFULLY.

30:12.033 --> 30:14.167
I CAN LOAD THIS BOAT
IF I GET LUCKY.

30:14.167 --> 30:16.600
THAT'S THE ONLY WAY
I'M GONNA GET HOME.

30:16.600 --> 30:18.800
AND THIS IS THE ONLY THING
STANDING BETWEEN ME

30:18.800 --> 30:20.300
AND LIVING RETIRED LIFE,

30:20.300 --> 30:23.733
HANGING OUT WITH GRANDBABIES,
GOING SPORTFISHING.

30:23.733 --> 30:25.767
SO, SEE WHAT WE'RE GONNA
GET OUT OF THIS.

30:25.767 --> 30:28.133
I'M HOPING FOR SOME 200s.

30:28.133 --> 30:31.100
200 AVERAGE WOULD
BE PRETTY GOOD.

30:33.467 --> 30:36.067
JUST NEED OUR CRABS
TO WORK WITH US HERE.

30:36.067 --> 30:37.567
COME ON, CRABBIES!

30:45.167 --> 30:46.767
WE'LL SEE WHAT HAPPENS.

30:46.767 --> 30:50.433
Johnathan:
COME ON! COME ON! COME ON!

30:50.433 --> 30:54.200
[ WHEEL GRINDING ]

30:54.200 --> 30:56.300
I SEE CRAB LEGS!

30:59.100 --> 31:01.067
OH, THERE'S CRAB LEGS.
I GOT CRAB LEGS.

31:01.067 --> 31:03.600
I GOT CRAB ON THE BACK.

31:03.600 --> 31:05.067
WE GOT CRAB LEGS.

31:05.067 --> 31:07.067
[ LAUGHS ]

31:07.067 --> 31:08.533
YEAH!

31:08.533 --> 31:10.433
I FEEL THE PRESSURE.

31:10.433 --> 31:12.533
YEAH!

31:12.533 --> 31:16.067
NO ESCAPE FOR THE OPIES.
NO ESCAPE FOR THE OPIES.

31:23.467 --> 31:25.833
Johnathan: 140.

31:25.833 --> 31:27.400
140 IN THAT ONE.

31:30.233 --> 31:32.067
NEED 200.

31:32.067 --> 31:34.267
SEE WHAT THE NEXT ONE'S GOT.

31:39.800 --> 31:43.467
COME ON, MAN! BETTER!
GIVE ME BETTER THAN THAT!

31:43.467 --> 31:44.633
OH, BABY.

31:50.567 --> 31:52.167
YEAH, BABY!

31:52.167 --> 31:54.367
I SEE SOME CRAB LEGS.

31:54.367 --> 31:56.667
YEAH! LOOK AT ALL
THESE CRAB LEGS!

31:56.667 --> 31:58.167
YEAH!

31:59.367 --> 32:00.733
[BLEEP] YEAH!

32:00.733 --> 32:02.833
YEAH, BABY! NO WAY!

32:02.833 --> 32:05.200
YEAH, BABY, BABY,
BABY, BABY!

32:05.200 --> 32:07.067
OH, MAN!
YOU COULD TASTE IT!

32:07.067 --> 32:09.733
[ SMACKING LIPS ]

32:09.733 --> 32:11.300
Narrator: ON THE CRAB...

32:11.300 --> 32:13.433
WE'RE GONNA BE OKAY.
[ KNOCKING ]

32:13.433 --> 32:15.467
ALL RIGHTY.

32:15.467 --> 32:16.533
YEAH, BABY!

32:16.533 --> 32:18.967
...CAPTAIN JOHNATHAN'S
RETIREMENT DREAM

32:18.967 --> 32:20.733
IS BECOMING A REALITY.

32:20.733 --> 32:22.700
THANK YOU, JESUS.

32:22.700 --> 32:25.300
[BLEEP] YOU, BYE BYE KITTY,
AND RAT.

32:25.300 --> 32:26.700
I LIKE THE RAT.

32:29.067 --> 32:31.067
3-6-5.

32:31.067 --> 32:33.400
365! YEAH!

32:33.400 --> 32:35.067
THAT'S WHAT WE WANT
TO SEE, NEAL.

32:35.067 --> 32:36.733
YEAH, 365.

32:36.733 --> 32:38.600
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

32:38.600 --> 32:39.967
LOOK AT THIS.

32:39.967 --> 32:42.333
OH! OH!

32:42.333 --> 32:44.400
HOLY MOLY!
WE'RE GONNA PLUG THE TANK!

32:46.333 --> 32:48.400
WE NAILED IT!
WE HIT IT AGAIN!

32:48.400 --> 32:49.867
[ LAUGHS ]

32:49.867 --> 32:52.133
LOOK, YOU CAN WALK ON THESE!

32:52.133 --> 32:54.200
[ LAUGHS ]

32:54.200 --> 32:55.900
[ INHALES ]

32:55.900 --> 32:57.567
NAMASTE.

32:57.567 --> 33:01.367
Man: YEAH, WE'RE GONNA FILL THIS
BOAT UP IN RECORD TIME, BABY!

33:01.367 --> 33:04.567
RECORD TIME!
JOHNNY, YOU'RE THE MAN!

33:04.567 --> 33:06.633
Johnathan: JUST GONNA START
PICKING THEM UP.

33:06.633 --> 33:09.567
IT'S LIKE BERRY PICKING,
BERRY PATCH.

33:09.567 --> 33:10.767
WHOO! YES!

33:10.767 --> 33:12.967
Narrator:
IN HIS 37 YEARS,

33:12.967 --> 33:16.867
THE WILY CAPTAIN HAS PICKED
OVER 22 MILLION POUNDS OF CRAB.

33:16.867 --> 33:18.367
LITTLE CRAB JIG.

33:18.367 --> 33:20.433
Narrator:
BUT WHO'S COUNTING?

33:20.433 --> 33:22.833
WE NEED A BIGGER TABLE!

33:22.833 --> 33:24.300
[ LAUGHS ]

33:24.300 --> 33:26.933
TIME BANDIT, 1, CRAB, 0.

33:27.967 --> 33:29.900
HELL, YEAH!

33:29.900 --> 33:31.533
THAT'S A GOOD POT, MAN!

33:31.533 --> 33:33.933
LOOK AT THAT.

33:33.933 --> 33:36.667
PRETTY PROUD MOMENT.

33:39.967 --> 33:41.133
YEAH, BABY!

33:41.133 --> 33:42.867
YEAH, BABY!

33:44.167 --> 33:46.600
WHOO!

33:46.600 --> 33:49.233
IT'S JUST CLEAN,
CLEAN, CLEAN FISHING.

33:49.233 --> 33:51.300
CLEAN, BEAUTIFUL, BRIGHT CRAB.

33:51.300 --> 33:53.300
NO SORTING. SCOOPERS.

33:53.300 --> 33:56.700
Narrator:
AFTER EIGHT HOURS SPENT
HAULING UP AN OPILIO BOUNTY...

33:56.700 --> 33:59.200
SEALING THE DEAL, BABY.
BOOP!

33:59.200 --> 34:02.333
Narrator:
...JOHNATHAN HILLSTRAND
CAN SEE THE END OF HIS SEASON

34:02.333 --> 34:04.833
AND THE END OF HIS
LEGENDARY CAREER.

34:04.833 --> 34:06.500
COME ON, BOY!

34:11.500 --> 34:13.933
WE LOVE YOU, JOHNATHAN!

34:13.933 --> 34:16.567
WE'RE HAVING SOME FUN.
THIS IS MY DREAM RIGHT HERE.

34:16.567 --> 34:18.433
THIS IS A DREAM.
I HAD A DREAM!

34:18.433 --> 34:20.900
YEAH!

34:20.900 --> 34:23.766
THESE ARE THE GOOD OL' DAYS
RIGHT HERE, RIGHT NOW.

34:23.766 --> 34:25.333
GOOD OL' DAYS ARE RIGHT NOW.

34:25.333 --> 34:29.233
[ WIND HOWLING ]

34:29.233 --> 34:31.900
OKAY, GUYS, THIS IS
THE LAST ONE COMING UP.

34:34.433 --> 34:37.667
I SWEAR TO GOD,
THIS IS THE LAST ONE.

34:40.667 --> 34:42.933
WHOO! YEAH, BABY!

34:42.933 --> 34:45.632
ROCKET MAN!

34:47.733 --> 34:51.766
HASN'T RESONATED
IN MY HEAD YET, BUT...

34:51.766 --> 34:54.167
[ SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY ]

34:54.167 --> 34:56.067
I DON'T BELIEVE THIS IS REAL.

35:00.533 --> 35:02.667
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

35:02.667 --> 35:05.333
IT CHOKES ME UP.

35:11.600 --> 35:14.733
Man: TODAY'S A REALLY SPECIAL
DAY FOR OUR CAPTAIN JOHNNY.

35:14.733 --> 35:16.333
WE TAKE OUR HAT OFF...

35:21.633 --> 35:24.767
[ Rapping ] * YEAH, YEAH, YEAH,
WHAT'S UP? WHAT'S UP? *

35:24.767 --> 35:26.433
WHAT YOU GOT?

35:26.433 --> 35:28.867
OH!

35:28.867 --> 35:31.267
LOOK AT THIS. OKAY.

35:31.267 --> 35:33.233
LOOK AT THIS.
DO THAT AGAIN.

35:33.233 --> 35:35.067
[ SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY ]

35:38.467 --> 35:40.700
[ LAUGHS ]

35:40.700 --> 35:43.900
**

35:47.833 --> 35:50.367
WE GOT IT,
WE GOT IT, WE GOT IT!

35:50.367 --> 35:51.900
OH!

35:55.800 --> 35:59.100
[ LAUGHING ]

36:01.600 --> 36:03.267
WE LOVE YOU, BOSS!

36:03.267 --> 36:05.333
LOVE YOU [BLEEP]

36:05.333 --> 36:07.833
I LOVE THESE GUYS.

36:09.867 --> 36:11.767
Narrator:
GOOD FRIENDS KEITH AND JOHN

36:11.767 --> 36:14.600
END THEIR SEASONS TOGETHER
AND ON TOP.

36:20.400 --> 36:22.800
Johnathan: OKAY, GUYS, THIS IS
THE LAST ONE COMING IN.

36:22.800 --> 36:24.367
Man: COME ON, BABY!

36:24.367 --> 36:27.700
Narrator:
ON THE TIME BANDIT...

36:27.700 --> 36:30.133
MY LAST POT I'LL EVER PULL.

36:30.133 --> 36:32.233
LAST TIME EVER.

36:32.233 --> 36:35.267
HERE WE GO!

36:35.267 --> 36:37.100
GET IN THERE, CHARLIE!

36:38.733 --> 36:39.900
LAST ONE, BABY!

36:39.900 --> 36:42.200
[BLEEP] YEAH!
WE'RE GOING HOME!

36:44.167 --> 36:46.367
Johnathan:
WE'RE DONE, LAST POT.

36:46.367 --> 36:48.433
-YEAH! YEAH!
-[BLEEP] YEAH, BABY!

36:48.433 --> 36:51.100
Narrator: AS THE FINAL CRAB POT
COMES ABOARD...

36:51.100 --> 36:53.567
WE LOVE YOU,
CAPTAIN JOHNATHAN!

36:53.567 --> 36:55.767
Johnathan:
I LOVE YOU, GUYS!

36:55.767 --> 37:01.333
Narrator:
...JOHNATHAN CLOSES OUT THE LAST
OF HIS 250,000-POUND QUOTA

37:01.333 --> 37:05.067
AND 37 YEARS IN THE BERING SEA.

37:05.067 --> 37:09.567
WE LOVE JOHN WITH ALL OUR HEART.
HE'S HELPED OUT MY FAMILY.

37:09.567 --> 37:12.067
HE'S HELPED OUT
ALL OF THESE GUYS.

37:12.067 --> 37:15.600
HE'S GIVEN US A GOOD JOB,
A GOOD NAME,

37:15.600 --> 37:18.567
SO THANK YOU, JOHNNY.
THANK YOU FOR EVERYTHING.

37:18.567 --> 37:20.767
-WE LOVE YOU, JOHN.
-WE LOVE YOU, JOHN!

37:20.767 --> 37:23.100
Narrator: THANKS TO
THE SKIPPER'S BIG FINISH,

37:23.100 --> 37:28.467
EACH DECKHAND WILL WALK
AWAY $65,000 RICHER.

37:28.467 --> 37:30.767
-HEY, BUDDY.
-CAPTAIN JOHNATHAN.

37:30.767 --> 37:33.400
HEY, THANK YOU, MAN,
FOR KEEPING ALL MY GUYS SAFE.

37:33.400 --> 37:34.533
THANK YOU.

37:34.533 --> 37:35.733
OH, NO, THANK YOU.

37:35.733 --> 37:37.433
-YEAH.
-REALLY, THANK YOU SO MUCH.

37:37.433 --> 37:39.167
I JUST WANT TO LET YOU
KNOW I APPRECIATE IT.

37:39.167 --> 37:40.867
THANK YOU, FREDDY, SO MUCH.
THANK YOU SO MUCH.

37:40.867 --> 37:42.300
A LOT OF RESPECT FOR YOU.

37:42.300 --> 37:44.733
-THANK YOU SO MUCH.
-WHAT YOU'VE DONE FOR ALL OF US.

37:44.733 --> 37:46.900
YOU KNOW, FOR 37 YEARS,

37:46.900 --> 37:48.933
FOR ALL THE FISHERMEN
THAT WORK FOR YOU,

37:48.933 --> 37:50.800
YOU KEEP IT --
FEED ALL THEIR FAMILIES.

37:50.800 --> 37:52.800
THANK YOU. THANK YOU, FREDDY.
YOU MADE IT SAFE.

37:52.800 --> 37:55.467
IT'S 'CAUSE OF YOU. I'M ONLY
AS GOOD AS THE GUYS ON DECK.

37:55.467 --> 37:57.300
I'M ONLY AS GOOD
AS THE GUYS ON DECK, MAN.

37:57.300 --> 38:00.067
LOVE YOU, BOSS. THANK YOU
SO MUCH FOR EVERYTHING.

38:00.067 --> 38:01.167
THANK YOU, FREDDY.

38:01.167 --> 38:02.400
LAST STRING EVER.

38:02.400 --> 38:04.433
-YES, LAST STRING EVER.
-THANK YOU SO MUCH, BOSS.

38:04.433 --> 38:05.967
SERIOUSLY,
THANK YOU, FREDDY!

38:05.967 --> 38:07.967
THANK YOU, BOSS!

38:07.967 --> 38:10.167
GOOD, GOOD GUY, MAN.

38:14.867 --> 38:16.133
[ PHONE RINGS ]

38:16.133 --> 38:18.500
[BLEEP] SCARES THE [BLEEP]
OUT OF ME EVERY TIME.

38:18.500 --> 38:20.200
LOUDER THAN [BLEEP]

38:20.200 --> 38:21.600
[ BEEP ]

38:21.600 --> 38:24.300
TIME BANDIT.

38:24.300 --> 38:26.933
HELLO, JOHNATHAN!

38:26.933 --> 38:30.233
[ SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY ]

38:30.233 --> 38:31.967
HEY, KEITH!

38:31.967 --> 38:34.100
WE GOT OUR CRAB POTS ON
AND WE'RE HEADED IN.

38:34.100 --> 38:36.300
WE GOT 20 OVER WHAT
WE'RE SUPPOSED TO CATCH

38:36.300 --> 38:37.567
FOR THE SEASON.

38:37.567 --> 38:40.900
NO ONE BELIEVES ME,
BUT THIS IS MY LAST SEASON,

38:40.900 --> 38:43.833
SO YOU KNOW,
I'M NOT COMING OUT HERE AGAIN.

38:43.833 --> 38:46.233
YOU KNOW WHAT? HERE.

38:46.233 --> 38:47.533
[ LAUGHS ]

38:47.533 --> 38:49.767
I'M GONNA BROADCAST
THIS TO THE FLEET.

38:49.767 --> 38:52.367
[ LAUGHS ] I KNOW I'M NOT
COMING BACK OUT HERE.

38:52.367 --> 38:53.433
[ RADIO STATIC ]

38:53.433 --> 38:55.833
I HAVE A REALLY
GOOD INNER PEACE,

38:55.833 --> 38:57.267
A PEACEFUL FEELING ABOUT IT.

38:57.267 --> 38:59.667
I BEEN HEARING THAT FOR THREE
YEARS, HE'S GONNA QUIT FISHING.

38:59.667 --> 39:02.433
I WONDER IF THIS IS IT.

39:02.433 --> 39:04.267
37 YEARS OUT HERE,

39:04.267 --> 39:06.267
AND MAN, JUST KNOW
WHEN IT'S TIME TO GO,

39:06.267 --> 39:07.900
AND IT'S TIME TO GO

39:07.900 --> 39:09.100
AND DO SOMETHING ELSE.

39:09.100 --> 39:12.067
[ LAUGHS ] UNREAL.

39:12.067 --> 39:14.400
Narrator:
AFTER MORE THAN THREE DECADES

39:14.400 --> 39:16.767
WITH CAPTAIN HILLSTRAND
AT THEIR SIDE...

39:16.767 --> 39:19.967
WE'RE ACTUALLY GONNA -- WE'RE
GONNA DO THE FLARES NOW, GUYS.

39:19.967 --> 39:21.833
MYLES, GO GRAB THE FLARES.

39:21.833 --> 39:25.100
...THE FLEET COMES TOGETHER
TO SALUTE THE SKIPPER...

39:25.100 --> 39:29.200
HEY, ED! CAN YOU
COME UP FOR A SEC?

39:29.200 --> 39:31.733
WE'LL GIVE THE GUY
A LITTLE SENDOFF, AS WELL.

39:31.733 --> 39:33.367
...TIME BANDIT STYLE.

39:33.367 --> 39:36.067
HE AND KEITH ARE HAVING
A LITTLE SAFETY MEETING,

39:36.067 --> 39:39.200
AND I THINK WE'RE GONNA
DO ONE OF OUR OWN.

39:39.200 --> 39:42.667
OH, YEAH! LET 'ER RIP, GUYS.
LET 'ER GO.

39:42.667 --> 39:44.100
LET 'ER GO!

39:44.100 --> 39:45.967
[ FLARES IGNITING ]

39:47.633 --> 39:49.067
HOLY SMOKES!

39:49.067 --> 39:51.600
YEAH, BABY, LOOK AT THAT!

39:51.600 --> 39:53.233
WHOO!

39:53.233 --> 39:55.500
[ CHEERING ]

39:55.500 --> 39:57.300
FOR THE TIME BANDIT!

39:57.300 --> 39:58.367
SEND 'EM OUT!

39:58.367 --> 40:00.533
[ FLARES IGNITING ]

40:00.533 --> 40:04.433
**

40:04.433 --> 40:07.100
CONGRATS, JOHNNY!
LOVE YOU, BROTHER!

40:07.100 --> 40:08.967
SHOWTIME.

40:08.967 --> 40:10.567
[ FLARES IGNITING ]

40:10.567 --> 40:12.733
IT'S LIT. THE WHOLE
PLACE IS LIT UP.

40:12.733 --> 40:14.967
[ LAUGHS ]
LOOK AT 'EM ALL.

40:14.967 --> 40:16.967
WHOO-HOO!

40:18.000 --> 40:19.333
[ EXPLOSION ]

40:19.333 --> 40:21.667
**

40:21.667 --> 40:24.300
* A PLACE THAT I CALL HOME *

40:24.300 --> 40:25.700
CEASE FIRE!

40:25.700 --> 40:28.233
* NO LAZY DAYS OR CRAZY JOBS *

40:28.233 --> 40:29.867
[ LAUGHS ]

40:29.867 --> 40:32.500
[ SINGING INDISTINCTLY ]

40:36.767 --> 40:38.167
[ GUNSHOTS ]

40:40.367 --> 40:44.700
* OH, OH, OH *

40:44.700 --> 40:48.100
* THEY SAY JOB IS NEVER DONE *

40:48.100 --> 40:49.600
[ LAUGHTER ]

40:49.600 --> 40:54.367
* LET'S GO HOME *

40:54.367 --> 40:57.800
* ANOTHER LIFE IS YET TO COME *

40:57.800 --> 41:00.700
* IS YET TO COME *

41:02.067 --> 41:03.567
YEAH! YEAH!

41:03.567 --> 41:06.067
[ LAUGHS ]

41:06.067 --> 41:07.900
IT CAN'T GET
MUCH BETTER THAN THIS!

41:07.900 --> 41:10.567
[ FIREWORKS EXPLODING ]

41:10.567 --> 41:12.733
THIS IS [BLEEP] CRAZY!

41:12.733 --> 41:20.233
* ANOTHER LIFE IS YET TO COME *

41:20.233 --> 41:23.067
THAT WAS PRETTY COOL,
I MUST SAY.

41:24.700 --> 41:28.400
HILLSTRAND, OUT!
HILLSTRAND!

